# Implement Instapaper-like Themes

The goal is to replicate the reading experience of Instapaper by implementing its four core color themes and adjusting the layout for a focus on readability.

## User Review Required

> [!NOTE]
> I will be defining four distinct themes in [src/styles/theme.css](file:///d:/yonggeun/porter/git/o-m.kr/src/styles/theme.css). I will set **Coffee** as the default for this branch to demonstrate the change.

## Proposed Changes

### Styles
#### [MODIFY] [theme.css](file:///d:/yonggeun/porter/git/o-m.kr/src/styles/theme.css)
- Define the four Instapaper themes using CSS variables.
- **Paper** (Classic):
  - Background: `#FDFDFD`
  - Text: `#222222`
- **Coffee** (Sepia):
  - Background: `#F8F1E3`
  - Text: `#5F4B32`
- **Gray** (Dark Gray):
  - Background: `#222222`
  - Text: `#AAAAAA`
- **Midnight** (OLED Black):
  - Background: `#000000`
  - Text: `#666666`

#### [MODIFY] [global.css](file:///d:/yonggeun/porter/git/o-m.kr/src/styles/global.css)
- Apply the **Coffee** theme variables to the `:root` or `body` by default.
- Adjust typography for an "Instapaper-like" impression:
  - Increase line-height.
  - Ensure comfortable max-width for reading.

